text: A general officer is an officer who is at a high military rank, usually in the army, and in some places, the air force. "General" is used in many countries around the world, and when a country uses a different word, there is another title that is of equal rank. Admiral is the corresponding rank in a navy. Usually an army has more than one "general officer" rank, and usually "general" is the highest of the general officer ranks. Category:Military ranks 1
title: General officer
